From b6151bddf8fbf2286c213eadb0f52df3e3fb253a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: 10BE Software UG <support@ns.10be.de>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 13:41:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Allow 10BE CarbCam to open the Carb Entry view with
 prefilled carbs

Adds a small URL-scheme entry point that lets 10BE CarbCam
(bundle de.be10.carbcam) hand its carb estimate over to Loop.
On URL receipt the standard carb entry sheet opens with carbs
and food type prefilled; the user must still tap Save before
anything is logged, and Loop's existing bolus prompt flow runs
afterwards unchanged.

Design notes:

  * URL scheme: carbcam-loop:// (registered in Info.plist next to
    the existing $(URL_SCHEME_NAME) entry, so Loop's own deeplinks
    keep working).
  * URL format: carbcam-loop://carbs?value=N&notes=...&source=...
  * Validation: value is required and clamped to 1..80 g, notes
    are truncated to 200 chars. Out-of-range or missing values
    cause the URL to be silently ignored.
  * The handler reuses Loop's existing NSUserActivity-based carb
    entry restoration path: it builds a NewCarbEntry, wraps it in
    an NSUserActivity.forNewCarbEntry(), and feeds it through
    rootViewController.restoreUserActivityState(_:) - the same
    mechanism Siri's NewCarbEntryIntent and the missed-meal
    notification already use. This means CarbEntryViewModel,
    RootNavigationController, and StatusTableViewController need
    zero changes.
  * Loop's carb entry UI does not have fat or protein fields, so
    if CarbCam sends those URL parameters they are intentionally
    ignored on the Loop side (unlike iAPS / Trio where they map
    1:1 to existing fields).
  * No silent CarbStore writes, no silent bolusing. All existing
    confirmation flows, validation, and bolus prompts remain
    completely unchanged.

Intent contract:

  scheme : carbcam-loop
  host   : carbs
  query  : value  (int,    required, 1..80, grams)
           notes  (string, optional, max 200 chars; used as Loop's
                   foodType field on the carb entry sheet)
           source (string, optional, free-form caller tag)
           fat    (int,    optional, ignored by Loop)
           protein(int,    optional, ignored by Loop)

Target branch: LoopKit/Loop main
